Reasoning: The paper deals with probabilistic models of language, specifically focusing on the sub-structure of words in morphologically complex languages. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses Bayesian models and distributed language models, which are commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the automatic learning of sub-word elements in unannotated lists of words, which could also fall under the sub-category of Deep Learning (cs.DL).
